Given an array of (pseudo) random numbers generated by the C++ function below, your task is to find the K-th smallest number of all the numbers.unsignedarray[5000000];voidrandomize(unsigneda,unsignedb,unsignedmod)
{for(inti=0;i<5000000;i++ )
	{a=31014* (a&65535) + (a>>16);b=17508* (b&65535) + (b>>16);array[i] = ((a<<16) +b) %mod;
	}
}Note that the computation might overflow, but we only care about the last 32 bit of each result so it doesn't matter.InputOne line with 4 numbers (a, b, mod, K) separated by space.0<a, b<655352<mod<232-11<K<5x106OutputK-th smallest number of all the generated numbers.ExampleInput:2 3 100000007 23Output:434
